                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 24074/3.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Vice and Deputy Consul General <persName type="from"
                            >Baugh</persName> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                        State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate General</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Hankow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1910-04-22">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 22, 1910</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Mr. Baugh reports serious disturbances Hunan missions and the destruction of
                    Chang-sha customhouse and business houses, Says missionaries have been summoned
                    from the interior, that foreign war vessels have been dispatched to Chang-sha,
                    and that the legation has been fully informed.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
